            <p>Newport<lb/>
                12<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Oct<hi rend="sup">r</hi> 1888<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev Dr S. Morais.<lb/>
                My dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>The bearer of this&#44; Mr G Mandel<lb/> has been residing here during the last two<lb/> summers&#44; pursuing his business as a vendor<lb/> of Turkish perfumes.  He is going to your city<lb/> &#38; begs me for a line of recommendation to you.<lb/>  I willingly write in his favor&#44; testifying that<lb/> he is a thoroughly observant Jew&#44; most faith<lb/>&#45;ful to his religions duties.  He may probably<lb/> seek your advice&#44; respecting the pursuit of his<lb/> occupation in your city &#38; desires me to say a<lb/> good word for him&#44; which may enlist your<lb/> interest in his well doing.  If you can at<lb/> any time aid him with your good counsel<lb/> you will be doing a charity to a very worthy<lb/> man &#38; you will additionally confer a perso<lb/>&#45;nal favor upon<lb/> Yours Very Faithfully<lb/> A P Mendes<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
